{"comments":"Attestation — Cryptographic proof of content at a point in time.\n\nAn Attestation is a composition of:\n- UUID5: Deterministic identifier derived from content\n- Timestamp: When the attestation was created\n- ContentHash: SHA-256 hash of the attested content\n\nThis is the core primitive for the Attestation pillar. It composes with\nany serializable content to provide cryptographic verification.\n\n## Why Attestation?\n\nAt billion-agent scale, agents need:\n- Proof that content existed at a specific time\n- Deterministic identity for deduplication\n- Tamper detection via content hashing\n- Foundation for digital signatures (x402, EIP-712)\n\n## Design Principles\n\n1. **Composable**: Attestation is a separate type that wraps content\n2. **Deterministic**: Same content + timestamp = same attestation\n3. **Verifiable**: Anyone can recompute the hash and check\n4. **Pure**: No side effects, no FFI\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"An attestation binding content to a point in time.\n\nComponents:\n- id: UUID5 derived from (namespace, contentHash || timestamp)\n- timestamp: When this attestation was created\n- contentHash: SHA-256 of the original content\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["id",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","UUID5"],"UUID5"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["timestamp",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Timestamp"],"Timestamp"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["contentHash",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Attestation"],"ContentHash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[98,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Attestation.purs","start":[94,1]},"title":"Attestation"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Attestation"],"ContentHash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[78,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Attestation.purs","start":[78,1]},"title":"eqContentHash"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Attestation"],"ContentHash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[79,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Attestation.purs","start":[79,1]},"title":"ordContentHash"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","Attestation"],"ContentHash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Attestation.purs","start":[81,1]},"title":"showContentHash"}],"comments":"SHA-256 hash of content being attested.\n\nThis is the cryptographic commitment to the content.\nIf the content changes, the hash changes.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[76,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/Attestation.purs","start":[76,1]},"title":"ContentHash"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create an attestation for string content at a given timestamp.\n\nThe content is hashed with SHA-256, and a deterministic UUID is\ng